    "causal_summary": "Cocoindex's `DEFAULT_INCLUDED_PATTERNS` (and the project-level `.cocoindex_code/settings.yml` mirroring it) include `.md`, `.mdx`, `.txt`, `.rst`. The result on this codebase: 45% of the index is non-code content. Worse, the 4-runtime skill mirror (Public has filesystem-level copies of every skill under `.opencode/skills/`, `.gemini/skills/`, `.claude/skills/`, `.codex/skills/`) means every SKILL.md / reference / playbook gets indexed 4 times. Cocoindex code search returns near-duplicate documentation hits where actual code matches should win.",
